Pendulum Dynamics Analysis  

• Modelled a simple pendulum system using Simscape Multibody to study dynamic motion behaviour
• Analysed system response under two conditions: zero damping and finite damping coefficient
• Observed continuous oscillations in the undamped case, while the damped system showed gradual decay in amplitude
• Visualized motion using simulation videos and examined angular position and angular velocity through scope plots
• Compared system behaviour to understand the effect of damping on energy dissipation and stability of motion
• Demonstrates practical understanding of oscillatory systems and real-world dynamic behaviour
